In[7]:
def train_model(model, train_loader, epochs, lr=1e-4):
    criterion, optimizer = nn.CrossEntropyLoss(), optim.Adam(model.parameters(), lr=lr)
    for epoch in range(epochs):
        model.train(); correct=total=train_loss=0
        for imgs, labels in tqdm(train_loader, desc=f"Epoch {epoch+1}/{epochs}"):
            imgs, labels = imgs.to(device), labels.to(device)
            optimizer.zero_grad()
            out = model(imgs)
            loss = criterion(out, labels)
            loss.backward(); optimizer.step()
            _, preds = torch.max(out,1)
            correct += (preds==labels).sum().item()
            total += labels.size(0)
            train_loss += loss.item()
        print(f"Epoch {epoch+1}/{epochs}: Acc {100*correct/total:.2f}%  Loss {train_loss/len(train_loader):.4f}")
    return model
In[8]:
def evaluate_metrics(model, loader, name):
    model.eval(); y_true=[]; y_pred=[]
    with torch.no_grad():
        for imgs,labels in loader:
            imgs,labels = imgs.to(device), labels.to(device)
            out = model(imgs)
            _,preds = torch.max(out,1)
            y_true.extend(labels.cpu().numpy())
            y_pred.extend(preds.cpu().numpy())
    acc  = accuracy_score(y_true,y_pred)
    prec = precision_score(y_true,y_pred,average='macro',zero_division=0)
    rec  = recall_score(y_true,y_pred,average='macro',zero_division=0)
    f1   = f1_score(y_true,y_pred,average='macro',zero_division=0)
    print(f"{name}: Acc={acc:.4f}  Prec={prec:.4f}  Rec={rec:.4f}  F1={f1:.4f}")
    return dict(Model=name, Accuracy=acc, Precision=prec, Recall=rec, F1=f1)

class CNN(nn.Module):
    def __init__(self):
        super().__init__()
        self.conv = nn.Sequential(
            nn.Conv2d(3,32,3,padding=1),nn.ReLU(),nn.MaxPool2d(2),
            nn.Conv2d(32,64,3,padding=1),nn.ReLU(),nn.MaxPool2d(2),
            nn.Conv2d(64,128,3,padding=1),nn.ReLU(),nn.MaxPool2d(2))
        self.fc = nn.Sequential(
            nn.Flatten(),
            nn.Linear(128*(IMG_SIZE//8)*(IMG_SIZE//8),256),
            nn.ReLU(),nn.Dropout(0.5),
            nn.Linear(256,NUM_CLASSES))
    def forward(self,x): return self.fc(self.conv(x))

from torchvision import models
import torch.nn.functional as F
import math

cnn_backbone = models.resnet18(pretrained=True)
cnn_backbone.fc = nn.Identity()

vit_backbone = models.vit_b_16(pretrained=True)
vit_backbone.heads = nn.Linear(vit_backbone.heads.head.in_features, NUM_CLASSES)

class CNN_ViT(nn.Module):
    def __init__(self, cnn, vit):
        super().__init__()
        self.cnn = cnn
        self.vit = vit
        self.conv1x1 = nn.Conv2d(512, 3, kernel_size=1)
        self.resize = nn.Upsample(size=(224,224), mode='bilinear')
        
    def forward(self, x):
        # CNN feature extraction
        feats = self.cnn.forward_features(x) if hasattr(self.cnn, "forward_features") else None
        if feats is None:
            feats = self.cnn.conv1(x)
            feats = self.cnn.bn1(feats)
            feats = self.cnn.relu(feats)
            feats = self.cnn.maxpool(feats)
            feats = self.cnn.layer1(feats)
            feats = self.cnn.layer2(feats)
            feats = self.cnn.layer3(feats)
            feats = self.cnn.layer4(feats)  # [B,512,H',W']
        
        feats = self.conv1x1(feats)       # [B,3,H',W']
        feats = self.resize(feats)        # [B,3,224,224]
        out = self.vit(feats)             # Full ViT pipeline
        return out

from math import pi

for i, row in results_df.iterrows():
    categories = ["Accuracy", "Precision", "Recall", "F1"]
    values = row[categories].tolist()
    values += values[:1]  # close the loop

    angles = [n / float(len(categories)) * 2 * pi for n in range(len(categories))]
    angles += angles[:1]

    plt.figure(figsize=(5,5))
    plt.polar(angles, values, marker='o', label=row["Model"])
    plt.fill(angles, values, alpha=0.25)
    plt.title(row["Model"])
    plt.xticks(angles[:-1], categories)
    plt.ylim(0,1)
    plt.show()

In[49]:






def get_face(img_path, fer_image=True):
    orig = np.array(Image.open(img_path).convert("RGB"))
    if fer_image:
        face_img = Image.fromarray(orig).convert("RGB").resize((299,299))
        bbox = (0,0,orig.shape[1], orig.shape[0])
        landmarks = None
    else:
        faces = detector(orig)
        if len(faces)==0:
            face_img = Image.fromarray(orig).convert("RGB").resize((299,299))
            bbox = (0,0,orig.shape[1], orig.shape[0])
            landmarks = None
        else:
            f = faces[0]
            landmarks_obj = predictor(orig, f)
            landmarks = [(landmarks_obj.part(i).x, landmarks_obj.part(i).y) for i in range(68)]
            x1,y1,x2,y2 = f.left(), f.top(), f.right(), f.bottom()
            crop = orig[y1:y2, x1:x2]
            face_img = Image.fromarray(crop).convert("RGB").resize((299,299))
            bbox = (x1,y1,x2,y2)
    return orig, face_img, bbox, landmarks





















In[50]:






class GradCAM:
    def __init__(self, model, target_layer):
        self.model = model
        self.gradients = None
        self.activations = None
        target_layer.register_forward_hook(self.save_activation)
        target_layer.register_backward_hook(self.save_gradient)
    def save_activation(self, module, inp, out):
        self.activations = out
    def save_gradient(self, module, grad_in, grad_out):
        self.gradients = grad_out[0]
    def generate(self, x, class_idx):
        self.model.zero_grad()
        out = self.model(x)
        out[0, class_idx].backward()
        grads = self.gradients.mean(dim=[2,3], keepdim=True)
        cam = (grads * self.activations).sum(dim=1, keepdim=True)
        cam = torch.relu(cam)
        cam = F.interpolate(cam, size=(299,299), mode='bilinear', align_corners=False)
        cam = cam.squeeze().detach().cpu().numpy()
        cam = (cam - cam.min()) / (cam.max() - cam.min() + 1e-8)
        return cam





















In[51]:






def batch_predict(images):
    model.eval()
    batch = torch.stack([transform(Image.fromarray(i)).to(device) for i in images], dim=0)
    with torch.no_grad():
        logits = model(batch)
        probs = F.softmax(logits, dim=1).cpu().numpy()
    return probs





















In[52]:






def model_predict_numpy(x_np):
    
    if x_np.dtype != np.float32:
        x_np = x_np.astype(np.float32)
    # normalize to [0,1] if needed
    if x_np.max() > 1.0:
        x_np = x_np / 255.0
    # apply mean/std normalization and change to CHW
    x_np = (x_np - mean.reshape(1,1,1,3)) / std.reshape(1,1,1,3)
    x_t = torch.from_numpy(x_np.transpose((0,3,1,2))).float().to(device)
    with torch.no_grad():
        out = model(x_t)
        probs = F.softmax(out, dim=1).cpu().numpy()
    return probs

In[63]:






def to_torch_input(np_imgs):
    # np_imgs: (N,H,W,3) float32 in 0..255 or 0..1
    arr = np_imgs.astype(np.float32)
    if arr.max() > 1.0:
        arr = arr / 255.0
    # normalize
    arr = (arr - mean.reshape(1,1,1,3)) / std.reshape(1,1,1,3)
    # to CHW
    t = torch.from_numpy(arr.transpose(0,3,1,2)).float().to(device)
    return t

    # each entry may be torch tensor or numpy

    if isinstance(first, torch.Tensor):
        shap_vals = [v.detach().cpu().numpy() for v in shap_vals]
else:
    # ndarray or tensor

        shap_vals = shap_vals.detach().cpu().numpy()





















In[68]:






if isinstance(shap_vals, list):
    # shap_vals[class_idx] -> shape (1, H, W, C) or (1, C, H, W)
    raw = shap_vals[pred_idx]  # choose predicted class
    raw = np.array(raw)
    # if shape is (1, C, H, W), move channel to last dim
    if raw.ndim == 4 and raw.shape[1] in (1,3):
        raw = raw.transpose(0,2,3,1)  # (1,H,W,C)
    shap_for_class = raw[0]  # (H,W,C)
else:
    arr = np.array(shap_vals)  # e.g. (1, classes, H, W, C) or (classes, 1, H, W, C)
    if arr.ndim == 5:
        if arr.shape[0] == 1 and arr.shape[1] == num_classes:
            shap_for_class = arr[0, pred_idx]  # (H,W,C)
        elif arr.shape[0] == num_classes and arr.shape[1] == 1:
            shap_for_class = arr[pred_idx, 0]  # (H,W,C)
        else:
            # fallback: try last dims
            shap_for_class = arr.reshape(-1, *arr.shape[-3:])[pred_idx]
    else:
        raise RuntimeError("Unexpected SHAP output shape: %s" % (arr.shape,))





















In[69]:






smin, smax = shap_for_class.min(), shap_for_class.max()
if smax - smin <= 1e-8:
    shap_norm = np.zeros_like(shap_for_class)
else:
    shap_norm = (shap_for_class - smin) / (smax - smin)
